Echo, KGHM, Warsaw Exchange: Central European Equity Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-10-10T06:17:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/echo-kghm-warsaw-exchange-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index gained 0.8 percent, the Czech PX Index
climbed 1.4 percent while  Hungary ’s BUX Index fell 2.5 percent.  Echo Investment SA (ECH)  : The property developer
controlled by Polish billionaire Michal Solowow was upgraded to
“buy” from “hold” at UniCredit SpA. Echo jumped 3.9 percent
to 3.51 zloty.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  : Poland’s copper producer
plans to spend 640 million zloty ($197 million) on buying out
its workers’ rights to annual allowances of coal, Parkiet
reported. KGHM advanced 5.5 percent to 136.5 zloty.  Warsaw Stock Exchange (GPW)  : The operator of central
 Europe ’s biggest equity market was raised to “buy” from
“neutral” at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. Its shares declined 2.9
percent to 43.2 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw 
 pkozlowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
